      <p>Classics always come back, good food is good food. I like to take the white and the yolks and grate them twice OR push them through a mesh colander&#8230; it yields such a creamy texture. I have also heard of Pierre Herme putting a hardboiled egg in a chocolate cake. I think you might like it.<br />Cheers.</p>
